OL,3,CHouse prices in Wales rise for first
OL,4,Ctime in over a year
OL,6,FThe average price of a home in Wales
OL,7,Fhas risen for the first time in over a
OL,8,Fyear, according to the Principality
OL,9,FBuilding Society.
OL,11,FAn average house is priced at
OL,12,F#236,369, according to its Wales House
OL,13,FPrice Index.
OL,15,FAfter five consecutive quarters of
OL,16,Ffalling prices, the society said it
OL,17,Fwas now seeing a recovery.
OL,19,FHowever, the average price of a home
OL,20,Fin Wales is still down 2.4% when
OL,21,Fcompared with the same period in 2023.
