OL,3,CHouse prices in Wales rise for first
OL,4,Ctime in over a year
OL,6,FThis marks the first time that prices
OL,7,Fhave increased since December 2022,
OL,8,Fwhen the peak average price of
OL,9,F#249,000 was recorded.
OL,11,FPrincipality's report says that the
OL,12,Fmajority of local authorities in Wales
OL,13,Freported higher prices between April
OL,14,Fand June for the first time since 2022.
OL,16,FWhile areas such as Merthyr Tydfil
OL,17,Fstill saw a drop in prices, areas like
OL,18,FBridgend and Ceredigion reported
OL,19,Fincreases of over 16%.
